<% content_for :section_title, "Email" %>

<p class="text-xl">Jumpstart Pro provides easy configuration for transaction email providers.</p>
<p>To enable a transactional email provider you can do so in the Application section of the Jumpstart Pro configuration wizard UI located at <%= link_to nil, "/jumpstart", target: :_blank, class: "link underline" %>.</p>

<%= link_to("https://jumpstartpro.b-cdn.net/jsp-transactional-email-config-wizard-v1.png", target: "_blank") do %>
  <%= image_tag "https://jumpstartpro.b-cdn.net/jsp-transactional-email-config-wizard-v1.png", class: "block mx-auto", alt: "Screenshot of Jumpstart Pro Application/transactional email provider configuration wizard", size: "800" %>
<% end %>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Transactional Email Services" %>
<p>We have looked up the configurations for several different transactional email providers so you don't have to waste time fiddling with configs.</p>

<ul>
  <li><%= link_to "Amazon SES", "https://aws.amazon.com/ses/", target: :_blank %></li>
  <li><%= link_to "Mailgun", "https://www.mailgun.com/", target: :_blank %></li>
  <li><%= link_to "Mailjet", "https://www.mailjet.com/", target: :_blank %></li>
  <li><%= link_to "Mandrill (Part of Mailchimp)", "https://mandrillapp.com/login/", target: :_blank %></li>
  <li><%= link_to "MailPace (Previously OhMySMTP)", "https://mailpace.com/", target: :_blank %></li>
  <li><%= link_to "Postmark", "https://postmarkapp.com/", target: :_blank %></li>
  <li><%= link_to "Sendgrid", "https://sendgrid.com/en-us", target: :_blank %></li>
  <li><%= link_to "Brevo (Previously SendinBlue)", "https://www.brevo.com/", target: :_blank %></li>
  <li><%= link_to "Bird (Previously Sparkpost)", "https://bird.com/api/email?sp=true", target: :_blank %></li>
</ul>

<p>To add credentials for your transactional email provider, check out <%= link_to "the Credentials section", credentials_docs_path, target: :_blank, class: "link underline" %> in the docs.</p>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Default From Email" %>
<p>We'll also configure your Rails app's default from email address for transactional emails sent by your app. This could be as simple as <code>noreply@example.com</code> or your support email address.</p>
<p>You can also include a name if you would like a pretty name in your emails such as <code>My App &lt;noreply@example.com&gt;</code></p>
